# `scripts/` is intended to be code (or code-adjacent docs).
# The root `.gitignore` contains broad directory-name ignores like `models/` and `data/`
# to avoid committing artifacts. Those rules should not hide code packages under `scripts/layers/**`.

# Keep any code packages named `models` tracked under layers
!layers/**/models/
!layers/**/models/**

# Keep any code packages named `data` tracked under layers
!layers/**/data/
!layers/**/data/**

# Keep cache as code when it lives under layers (runtime caches elsewhere remain ignored by root rules)
!layers/**/cache/
!layers/**/cache/**

